{{Title|attachment (scripts)}}
{{Header|Modding|Scripts}}
{{Page version|42.10.0}}
The '''attachment''' script block is used to define the parameters for attaching a [[model (scripts)|model]] to a specific bone of another model, typically used for [[item (scripts)|items]] that are held or worn by characters but this is also used for [[vehicle (scripts)|vehicles]].

When defining an attachment script, it is not named with a unique name like other script types but instead is named after available attachment points which are listed in the section [[#Attachment points]].
{{CodeSnip
| lang = Java
| code =
model upperScriptDefinition
{
    ...
    attachment attachmentPointName
    {
        ...
    }
    ...
}
}}

==Parameters==
{| class="wikitable theme-blue"
|+ style="white-space:nowrap" | List of parameters for the <code>attachment</code> block
! Parameter name !! Description !! Example
|-
| style="padding: 10px;text-align: center;"| <code>bone</code>
| The name of the bone to which the model is attached to.
| {{CodeSnip
| lang = java
| code =
bone = Bip01_L_Hand,
}}
|-
| style="padding: 10px;text-align: center;"| <code>offset</code>
| The position offset of the model relative to the bone. This is a vector in the format <code>x y z</code>.
| {{CodeSnip
| lang = java
| code =
offset = -0.0300 -0.1020 0.1210,
}}
|-
| style="padding: 10px;text-align: center;"| <code>rotate</code>
| The rotation of the model relative to the bone. This is a vector in the format <code>x y z</code>. The values are degrees.
| {{CodeSnip
| lang = java
| code =
rotate = -60.0000 -49.0000 -3.0000,
}}
|-
| style="padding: 10px;text-align: center;"| <code>scale</code>
| The scale of the model. This is a single float value.
| {{CodeSnip
| lang = java
| code =
scale = 0.5,
}}
|}

